Transaction are operations/ groups of operations performed on a database
All transactions in databse must maintain their ACID properties.
Those being Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, and Durability.
Atomic/ity- Each transaction is treated as a single operation
Consistency- Each transaction must follow rules of database
Isolation- Transaction can run concurrently as long as they 
don't ineract with each other
Durability- after a transaction successfully completes, changes to data persist and are not undone, even in the event of a system failure. (Use of a change log)